{
    "publish_date": "2012-11-16T02:01:24.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT2M37S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "At my house, no\nThanksgiving dinner", 
            "dur": "1.61", 
            "start": "0.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is complete without\nmathed potatoes.", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "2.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To make mathed potatoes,\nstart by boiling the potatoes", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "4.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until they&#39;re soft, which will\ntake about 15 to 20 minutes.", 
            "dur": "2.621", 
            "start": "8.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After you drain them and\nlet them cool slightly,", 
            "dur": "1.999", 
            "start": "10.831"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;re ready for the math.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "12.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Take one potato\nand divide evenly", 
            "dur": "1.789", 
            "start": "14.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to get half a potato,\nplus half a potato.", 
            "dur": "2.681", 
            "start": "16.239"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then divide the halves into\nfourths and the fourths", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "18.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into eights and so on.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "21.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eventually, you will have\na completely mathed potato", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "22.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that looks like this.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "25.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once you have proven this\nresult for one potato,", 
            "dur": "2.094", 
            "start": "26.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can apply it\nto other potatoes", 
            "dur": "1.416", 
            "start": "28.304"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "without going through\nthe entire process.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "29.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s how math works.", 
            "dur": "0.979", 
            "start": "31.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "While I prefer refined\nand precise methods", 
            "dur": "2.511", 
            "start": "32.759"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for mathing a\npotato, many people", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "35.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "just apply brute\nforce algorithms.", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "37.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can also add other variables\nlike butter, cream, garlic,", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "39.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "salt, and pepper.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "41.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Place in a hemisphere\nand garnish", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "42.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with an organic\nhyperbolic plane,", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "44.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and your math potatoes\nare ready for the table.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "46.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Together with a cranberry\ncylinder and a nice basket", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "48.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of bread spheres\nwith butter prism,", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "51.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;ll be well on\nyour way to creating", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "53.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a delicious and engaging\nThanksgiving meal.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "55.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s a serving tip.", 
            "dur": "1.35", 
            "start": "57.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When arranging mathed\npotatoes on your plate,", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "58.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is important to do it\nin a way that holds gravy.", 
            "dur": "2.76", 
            "start": "61.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you just make a mound,\nthe gravy will fall off.", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "63.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s best to create some\nkind of trough or pool.", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "66.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what shape will maximize\nthe amount of gravy it can hold?", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "68.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Due to the structural\nproperties of mathed potatoes,", 
            "dur": "2.595", 
            "start": "71.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this can essentially be reduced\nto a two-dimensional gravy pool", 
            "dur": "3.255", 
            "start": "74.035"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "problem, where you\nwant the most gravy", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "77.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "area given a certain\npotato perimeter.", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "78.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When I think of this\nquestion, I like", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "81.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to think about inflating shapes.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "83.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Say you inflated a triangle.", 
            "dur": "1.53", 
            "start": "85.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It would add more area and\nround out into a circle.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "86.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then, if the perimeter\ncan&#39;t change, it would pop.", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "88.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, all 2D shapes\ninflate into circles.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "91.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in 3D, it&#39;s spheres, which\nis my bubbles like to be round.", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And turkeys are\nspheroid, because that", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "98.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "optimizes for maximum stuffing.", 
            "dur": "2.56", 
            "start": "99.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The limited three-dimensional\ncapacity of mathed potatoes", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "102.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "may confuse things a little.", 
            "dur": "1.33", 
            "start": "104.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But since a mathed potato\nsphere can&#39;t support itself,", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "106.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;re really stuck with\nextrusions of 2D shapes.", 
            "dur": "2.472", 
            "start": "108.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So what&#39;s better?", 
            "dur": "0.708", 
            "start": "111.312"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A deep mathed potato cylinder\nor a shallow but wider one?", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "112.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, think of it like this.", 
            "dur": "1.36", 
            "start": "115.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you slice the\ndeep version in half,", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "117.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;ll see it has equivalent\ngravy-holding capacity to two", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "119.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "separate shallow cylinders.", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "122.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the perimeter\nof two circles would", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "125.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be more efficient if combined\ninto one bigger circle.", 
            "dur": "3.31", 
            "start": "126.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the solution is to create\nthe biggest, roundest,", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "130.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "shallowest gravy pool you can.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "132.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, maybe you should\njust skip the mathed potatoes", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "134.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and get a bowl.", 
            "dur": "1.26", 
            "start": "136.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anyway, I hope\nthis simple recipe", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "138.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "helps you have an optimal\nThanksgiving experience.", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "139.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Advanced\nchef-amaticians may wish", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "142.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to try Banach-Tarski\npotatoes, wherein", 
            "dur": "2.08", 
            "start": "144.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "after you cut a potato\nin a particular way,", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "146.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you put the pieces back\ntogether and get two potatoes.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "148.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Stay tuned for more delicious\nand extremely practical", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "151.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thanksgiving recipes this week.", 
            "dur": "2.773", 
            "start": "153.53"
        }
    ], 
